docs.lead_paragraph: The 11-day strike by building janitors that has left office workers to clean their own toilets and empty their own trash in 1,000 Manhattan office towers is casting a shadow that reaches far beyond New York City. It presents the first big test for John J. Sweeney, the A.F.L.-C.I.O.'s new president -- and whether the strikers win or lose, union leaders and labor experts say, it could set a pattern for unions nationwide.
